	<p>
		Before we continue, I'm going to need an idea of how familiar you are
		with digital technology. My recommendations will vary quite wildly
		depending on your level of tech literacy, and I want to make sure I'm
		not tossing anything at you that you're not ready for. Select the level
		of tech literacy that best applies to you:
	</p>
	<TechLiteracySelector client:load className="mb-4" />
	<p>
		After that, I need to know some specifics about what you use social
		media for:
	</p>

	<p>
		I'll use your answers to this to decide what parts of the guide to show
		you and what order to show you them in. After you've answered those
		questions, we can move on to talking about <i>the technology</i>.
	</p>
	<p>
		(P.S. if there's a use case you have for social media that wasn't
		covered here, *please* let me know about it by shooting an email to <a
			href="mailto:unplatform@fromthesuperhighway.com"
		>
			unplatform@fromthesuperhighway.com.
		</a>
	</p>
